{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ποτός</b>, ή, όν, <br /> (πίνω) <b>drunk, for drinking,</b> τί κακὸν ἐδανὸν ἢ ποτὸν πασαμένα..; [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 1408 (Lyric poetry); φάρμακον 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hippolytus” 516; ὕδωρ 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 6.100. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>substantive</i>, <b>ποτόν</b>, τό, <b>that which one drinks, drink,</b> especially of wine, κρητῆρας ἐπεστέψαντο ποτοῖο [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 1.470, etc.; θεῖον ποτὸν ἐντὸς ἔχοντες 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 2.341; κρόμυον ποτῷ ὄψον 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 11.630 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; of wine, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Persae” 615, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 703; τῷ ποτῷ χρησαμένους 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.121 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>].δ; σῖτα καὶ ποτά meat and <b>drink,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 5.34, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 2.3.27; βρωτοῖσι καὶ ποτοῖσι 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Supplices” 1110; σιτία καὶ π. 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Protagoras” 334a, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>drinking water,</b> ἰὼ Σκαμάνδρου πάτριον π. <b>water</b> of Sc.<b>drunk</b> by my sires, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 1157 (Lyric poetry); Σπερχειὸς ἄρδει πεδίον εὐμενεῖ π. [prev. author] “Pers.” 487; π. κρηναῖον 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 21, compare 1461 (_anapaest meter_)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ποτάμια π. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “fragment” 659.5. \">Refs</a>]","strongNumber":"G8874","accentedUnicode":"ποτός","shortDef":"a beverage","mediumDef":"a beverage","stepGloss":"a beverage","stepTransliteration":"potos","count":0,"_step_Type":"